\n<p>The project offers to different types of benefit. On one side, it provides trainings to women to develop new skills and a better understanding about newly created professions. On the other side, it fosters companies to increase the presence of women within their employees. Training is the main driver: we strongly believe that education is the key to open all doors.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The company was founded in Bologna in 2014, thanks to the support of TIM #WCAP: a Telecom Italia program that rewards and supports innovative business projects. Over the years, around these issues, we have built a national and international network that has given us the opportunity to achieve numerous awards and work alongside large companies that operate in the digital and technological innovation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We do online trainings through our platform, and vis-a-vis, addressed to women, and to companies\' employees and management.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We also carry out digital literacy program for women refugees and foreign women in order to offer them a different option to enter our job market and a different point of view about the job opportunities in the country.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks to projects such as this, we gained the WELCOME Logo issued by the UNHCR; we have been during 2017 one of the companies who facilitated the refugees integration in the job market in Italy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We care about diversity to convert it in equality: our aim is to create an equal environment, where men and women can work together to improve our lives, to increase our economy and improving our society.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','WORK WIDE WOMEN','','publish','open','open','','work-wide-women','','','2019-06-24 11:27:32','2019-06-24 11:27:32','',0,'http://lu.dev.europa.eu/wordpress/?pos